This probability is calculated as \(\frac{2}{3}\) after considering the expectation of \(t_1 + t_2\) given \(t_1 + t_2 < 1\). - Given that she stops at step 3, the probability that her position \(x_1 + x_2 + x_3 > 1\) is \(\frac{5}{6}\) (the probability that the sum of three independent uniform variables exceeds 1). - Therefore, the combined probability for stopping at step 3 is \(\frac{2}{3} \times \frac{5}{6} = \frac{5}{18}\). 3. **Completing all three steps**: - The probability that she completes all three steps (i.e., \(t_1 + t_2 + t_3 > 1\)) is \(\frac{1}{6}\).
